# CLAUDE.md — SentinelGuard Frontend Build Instructions

> You are a senior frontend engineer building a production-ready Next.js 14 application
> for SentinelGuard — a real-time on-chain security and exploit response layer for
> Solana DeFi protocols. Read this entire file before writing a single line of code.

---

## 0. Project Context (Read First)

SentinelGuard watches Solana DeFi protocols in real time. When an exploit is detected
(flash loan drain, TVL velocity drop, bridge outflow spike), it autonomously submits a
`pause_withdrawals` instruction to an Anchor smart contract on-chain — freezing the
protocol before funds are fully drained. The entire detect-to-pause loop runs in ~2–3
seconds on localnet and sub-500ms on mainnet with Yellowstone gRPC.

**Live system facts (use these everywhere, never use placeholder data):**
- Watcher pubkey: `EbVbJDyHdwoFZLxK7Ak8M4ta7hvJQthmBaGehd2VYa7m`
- SentinelState PDA: `2oQ8Z6ua6jCyXxEzGMz4gaENSauY75EY46XUbvyzmt8q`
- Vault address: `92mgS7mhu6hmJztUgJWef2gxu4zP3Pezm26MtNRQg1q9`
- Mock Protocol Program: `3Eue3cN8zMkeCHLiy6KNNSi6AjKdDfJTBsME4md3xcaC`
- Sentinel Program: `2Fi9UPVbD77Cr2SerjKkpPtbejYXdaa6D4R3Pjor4kQs`
- Detection rules: FLASH_LOAN_DRAIN (R1), TVL_VELOCITY (R2), BRIDGE_OUTFLOW_SPIKE (R3)
- Severity scale: 0–100. CRITICAL ≥90, HIGH 75–89, MEDIUM 60–74
- Confirmed pause signatures from live runs:
  - `3sX4PLsGqo9rhVCZ1vRWRoK9kx7VNkkYfrDmrDnjgNHHawpeK7MqccZxVJesYp8N9XDUyeNYxvoZuCU5rYyet3F8`
  - `28wPiUdajetVddnuKq7NHqMVfgRcrYxKccq1E1vAjRuwCsH2LRQDbBRvTi9sz5XuFtPZm7Vk1SYUDARFMAHZMsou`

---

## 1. Tech Stack

```
Framework:     Next.js 14 (App Router, TypeScript)
Styling:       Tailwind CSS + custom CSS variables
Charts:        Recharts
Components:    shadcn/ui (only where needed — avoid over-using it)
Solana:        @solana/web3.js
DB client:     postgres.js (not prisma — keep it lean)
Fonts:         Google Fonts — use distinctive pairing, NOT Inter/Roboto/Arial
Icons:         lucide-react
Animations:    Framer Motion for page transitions, CSS for micro-interactions
```

---

## 2. Design System

### 2.1 Theme — LIGHT ONLY, NO DARK MODE

This is a security monitoring tool used by protocol teams during incidents.
Light theme only. Think Bloomberg Terminal meets Linear — clean, precise,
information-dense without being cluttered.

```css
:root {
  /* Backgrounds */
  --bg-base:        #f8f7f4;   /* warm off-white, not pure white */
  --bg-surface:     #ffffff;   /* cards, panels */
  --bg-subtle:      #f1f0ed;   /* secondary panels, table rows alt */
  --bg-inset:       #e8e7e3;   /* code blocks, badges */

  /* Borders */
  --border-default: #e2e0db;
  --border-strong:  #c9c6bf;

  /* Text */
  --text-primary:   #1a1916;   /* near-black, warm */
  --text-secondary: #6b6860;   /* muted */
  --text-tertiary:  #9c9891;   /* very muted, timestamps */

  /* Brand */
  --brand-primary:  #0d7c4d;   /* deep forest green — security/trust */
  --brand-light:    #e8f5ee;   /* green tint backgrounds */
  --brand-border:   #a8d5bc;   /* green borders */

  /* Semantic — Alerts */
  --severity-critical-bg:     #fff1f0;
  --severity-critical-border: #fca5a5;
  --severity-critical-text:   #b91c1c;
  --severity-critical-dot:    #ef4444;

  --severity-high-bg:         #fff7ed;
  --severity-high-border:     #fed7aa;
  --severity-high-text:       #c2410c;
  --severity-high-dot:        #f97316;

  --severity-medium-bg:       #fefce8;
  --severity-medium-border:   #fde68a;
  --severity-medium-text:     #92400e;
  --severity-medium-dot:      #eab308;

  --severity-safe-bg:         #f0fdf4;
  --severity-safe-border:     #86efac;
  --severity-safe-text:       #15803d;
  --severity-safe-dot:        #22c55e;

  /* Status */
  --status-paused:    #ef4444;
  --status-active:    #22c55e;
  --status-watching:  #0d7c4d;

  /* Shadows */
  --shadow-sm:  0 1px 2px rgba(26,25,22,0.06);
  --shadow-md:  0 4px 12px rgba(26,25,22,0.08);
  --shadow-lg:  0 8px 32px rgba(26,25,22,0.10);
}
```

### 2.2 Typography

```css
/* Display font: DM Serif Display — authoritative, editorial */
/* Body font: DM Sans — clean, geometric, modern */
/* Mono font: JetBrains Mono — for addresses, hashes, code */

--font-display: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif;
--font-body:    'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
--font-mono:    'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
```

Import in layout.tsx:
```html
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display:ital@0;1&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
```

### 2.3 Layout Principles

- Max content width: 1280px, centered
- Sidebar: 240px fixed left, white background, subtle right border
- Main content: fluid, padding 32px
- Cards: white bg, 1px border, 8px radius, shadow-sm
- Section spacing: 48px between major sections
- NO full-bleed dark sections on landing page
- Use generous whitespace — security tools need breathing room

