## 5. Landing Page (/) — Detailed Spec

The landing page is the first thing judges see. It must communicate the project
in under 10 seconds of reading. Use real data, real tx signatures, real numbers.

### 5.1 Navbar
```
Left:  Shield icon + "SentinelGuard" in DM Serif Display
Right: "Documentation" | "GitHub" | "Launch Dashboard →" (green button)
Style: white bg, 1px bottom border, sticky, height 64px
```

### 5.2 Hero Section

Layout: Two columns, 55/45 split.

**Left column (text):**
```
Eyebrow (small caps, brand green):
  REAL-TIME SOLANA SECURITY

H1 (DM Serif Display, 56px, warm black, 2 lines max):
  "Detect exploits.
   Pause protocols.
   Save funds."

Body (DM Sans, 18px, secondary text, max 3 lines):
  SentinelGuard watches every Solana transaction in real time.
  When a flash loan drain or TVL attack is detected, it autonomously
  submits a pause instruction on-chain — in under 3 seconds.

CTA buttons (row):
  [Launch Dashboard →]  (filled, brand green)
  [View on GitHub]      (outlined)

Social proof row below CTAs:
  ✓ 5 attack scenarios tested    ✓ 2 rule types confirmed    ✓ Sub-3s response
```

**Right column (visual):**
Build an animated "live alert card" that cycles through real alerts.
This is NOT an image — it's actual JSX that simulates the live feed.

