## 15. Quality Checklist (before considering done)

- [ ] Landing page communicates the project in under 10 seconds
- [ ] All addresses are real (from constants.ts), never placeholder
- [ ] All API routes handle errors gracefully (try/catch, proper status codes)
- [ ] Loading skeletons shown while fetching, never blank white
- [ ] AddressBadge copy works in all browsers
- [ ] ExplorerLink opens correct Solana Explorer URL with cluster param
- [ ] TVL chart renders even with empty data (show "Waiting for data...")
- [ ] Alert feed shows "Watching for threats..." when no recent alerts
- [ ] Unpause button disabled when protocol is already active
- [ ] Mobile: sidebar collapses to hamburger at < 768px
- [ ] No dark mode anywhere (light only, as specified)
- [ ] Fonts loaded: DM Serif Display, DM Sans, JetBrains Mono
- [ ] No Inter, Roboto, or system-ui as primary fonts
- [ ] Page transitions feel smooth (Framer Motion layout animations)
- [ ] Console has no errors in production build

---

## 16. What NOT to do

- Do NOT use a dark theme anywhere
- Do NOT use placeholder addresses like "0x1234..." — use real constants
- Do NOT use Inter or Roboto as the primary font
- Do NOT stack the entire dashboard into one vertical column
- Do NOT show an empty white panel while loading — always skeleton
- Do NOT use purple gradients (cliché AI aesthetic)
- Do NOT hardcode TVL or alert counts — always fetch from API
- Do NOT use `<img>` tags for the architecture diagram — build it in JSX
- Do NOT add authentication — this is an internal tool
- Do NOT use `any` types in TypeScript — define proper interfaces in types.ts
```